Oh, God. Excuse me. Here, l'll get...

250
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:40,073
lf you two are done fooling around,
maybe we can go home?

251
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,878
Yeah...

252
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:46,875
Give me a few minutes, Junior.
l think the swelling's coming back.

253
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,996
l'll put a warm compress on that.

254
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:53,230
You're such a good little soldier.

255
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:59,516
''Give me a few minutes, Junior.''
''Give me a few minutes, Junior.''

256
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:02,399
l've been here for an hour!

257
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:04,994
Who does that nurse think she is?

258
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,998
- [music intro: Bad to the Bone]
- Mm...

259
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:10,515
l wouldn't do that if l were you.

260
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:12,830
Oh, it's you. Buzz off.

261
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,231
l wouldn't do that if l were you.

262
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:21,670
lf l were you, l wouldn't do a lot of things.
Like go out in public.

263
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:33,071
Next time, you'll listen to me.

264
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:42,949
Oh, my God, he's an Adonis!

265
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,951
Look at these stats!

266
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:46,792
Six feet tall.

267
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:49,190
1 85 pounds.

268
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:53,319
ln-seam, 35 inches.
Sweet Jesus, take me home!

269
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,433
What's this thing?

270
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,113
His son.

271
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:05,710
''Boy and convicted killer go on joyride''?

272
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:10,070
''Little league team hospitalised''?

273
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:14,109
''Union Carbide plant explodes''?

274
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,712
This kid's a nightmare.

275
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:19,235
Do you want to forget the whole thing?

276
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:21,231
Smith...

277
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:23,950
When someone has a bum leg,

278
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:26,475
you don't shoot the patient.

279
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:29,200
You just cut off the leg.

280
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:36,793
That's why you want a franchise. Big Ben is
the fastest-growing sports equipment empire.

281
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:38,871
Hey, it's Big Ben.

282
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:40,917
Pick up that phone and call now.

283
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:44,356
For just $399,
you can get one of my starter kits.

284
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:48,911
Then you'll be on your way to having it all,
just like me, Big Ben Healy.

285
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:51,196
What's this?

286
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:56,598
Look at this. What sort of idiot
would send Grandpa money?

287
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:58,671
That's my namel

288
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:01,798
- The old man's finally lost his mind.
- Uh-huh.

289
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:06,159
- Come downstairs. l got a surprise for you.
- All right! A surprise?

290
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:07,958
- Where is it?
- Down the steps.

291
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:10,714
Now, where is that surprise?

292
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,996
- Surprise!
- Hi, Junior!

293
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:17,233
l'm Rhoda, your babysitter.
We're gonna be good friends.

294
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:20,039
Dad, let's slow this down a minute.

295
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,316
Now, what is going on here?

296
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:25,756
This is Rhoda, your babysitter.
You're gonna be good friends.

297
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:29,117
Yeah, l heard that part. But why?

298
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:31,157
Yoo-hoo!

299
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:33,231
Because l'm going out on a date.

300
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,991
Hi, Ben. l'm all ready.

301
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:39,755
Great. Junior, you remember
Debbie Claukinski?

302
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:43,595
How can l forget? Her pie gave us the runs.

303
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:48,873
That's not true.
He's thinking about someone else's pie.

304
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:53,158
Anyway, we don't want to be late.
l got reservations at the Saint Pierre Club.

305
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:58,235
Oh, l'm so excited! My ex-husband
never took me to fancy places.

306
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:03,155
Not that l'm a gal who rattles on about her
last marriage. That guy is insanely jealous.

307
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:05,709
Dad, stay here and have fun with me.

308
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:07,871
Junior, you're gonna have fun with Rhoda.

309
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:12,909
l'm sure you can think of a lot of fun games
to play with her, OK? l'll talk to you later.

310
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:17,031
Welcome to the wonderful world of pigs.

311
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:20,272
Dirty, hungry and always horny,

312
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:23,796
they're Mother Nature's
clowns of the farm world.

313
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:27,350
Watching these charming critters
roll in the mud,

314
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:31,638
it's hard to believe they have an intelligence
as high as some humans.

315
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,791
But it's true.

316
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,633
Goodnight, Dad.

317
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:39,360
Hey, brat. Put that back. l'm watching.

318
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,870
This babysitter sucks.

319
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:49,873
l gotta get Dad back on track here.

320
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:54,828
l wonder whatever happened
to Mr Claukinski?

321
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:03,471
[phone]

322
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,199
Hello?

323
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:11,751
[Junior] Are you the guy that was married
to Debbie Claukinski?

324
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:14,388
Yeah, but then she left me.

325
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:20,151
She took my house, my money and my pride.

326
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:24,999
Well, l thought you'd like to know
that she found herself a new guy

327
00:22:25,160 --> 00:22:30,393
and they're out at the Saint Pierre Club,
having fun at your expense.

328
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:31,879
Who is this?

329
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:34,873
Just call me a friend.

330
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:39,552
[piano: upbeat rhythm]

331
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,352
Ben, this evening is perfect.

332
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:50,433
l know why the Mortville Gazette gave
this restaurant three and a half forks.

333
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:54,636
- Excuse me, we have a dress code.
- Let me in, you fool.

334
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:58,756
To us.

335
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,592
Tonight.

336
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:05,830
Ah-ha!

337
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:09,117
Debbie, you tramp! What are you doing here?

338
00:23:09,280 --> 00:23:11,840
l'm a free woman. l can do what l want.

339
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,558
l show you.

340
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:18,949
Debbie, you leave with me.
Come, we take the bus home.

341
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:21,759
Like hell l will. l'm on a date.

342
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:26,117
You home-breaker!

343
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:30,991
Oh, my kidney!

344
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,230
You bully!

345
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:38,994
Ben, shame on you!

346
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,635
Laser cannon locked on.

347
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:45,949
Fire laser cannon.

348
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:54,000
Finally, Dad's home.

349
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:55,513
[game bleeps]

350
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:59,391
- l thought you'd never get here.
- Who's that weirdo?

351
00:23:59,560 --> 00:24:03,758
- Gee, baby, you work fast.
- l got Russian hands and Roman fingers.

352
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:06,275
Now where's that master bedroom?

353
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,715
Here it is, darlin'!

354
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:15,439
- This ain't no motel.
- Mind your own beeswax, twerp. Go watch TV.

355
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:17,989
Yeah, what she said.

356
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:21,552
[music intro: Bad to the Bone]

357
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:34,719
Voytek, you were always the best.

358
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:36,359
Yeah.

359
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:40,155
So much for my first date.

360
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:43,400
[man yelling]

361
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:45,233
Now what?

362
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,435
All right!

363
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:49,239
[man] Yeah...go!

364
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:54,109
[man] Yes! That's great!

365
00:24:54,280 --> 00:24:55,793
Look at that.

366
00:24:57,400 --> 00:25:00,119
l didn't think people could do that.

367
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:02,669
She ain't no real blonde.

368
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,995
Come on!

369
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:09,118
Keep it up, my God!

370
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:15,754
- He's still going!
- Unbelievable.

371
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:22,073
Yeah, go for it!

372
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:24,800
Healy, that's hot stuff.

373
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:30,554
Junior, we're new here in this community.

374
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:33,712
Can't we at least attempt to fit in?

375
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:37,555
Why are you getting angry at me?
l didn't do it, l watched it.

376
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:40,359
Yes, and so did the entire neighbourhood.

377
00:25:40,520 --> 00:25:42,351
l didn't hear any complaints.

378
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:44,238
[knocking]

379
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:47,676
Great. The evening that wouldn't die.

380
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:49,879
What?

381
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:53,231
There's two more outside.

382
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:57,154
- Dad, what are you doing here?
- l thought l'd spend my vacation with you.

383
00:25:57,320 --> 00:26:00,312
- Excuse me?
- How did he find us?

384
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:03,873
You rascal. l even brought Nippy.

385
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:07,112
Hey, boy. Come here, Nip.

386
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:09,271
Get this freak off me! Get!

387
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:13,752
Don't scare him, for God's sakes.
He's only trying to be friendly.

388
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:17,071
- You know this dog is unbalanced.
- Get him out of here.

389
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:18,958
Nippy, stay.

390
00:26:19,680 --> 00:26:21,238
What is going on here?

391
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:25,996
You never take vacations, and if you did
you wouldn't spend them with me.

392
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,878
Little Ben.

393
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:31,918
Little Ben, you're my only son.

394
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:35,993
- Dad, you hate me.
- OK, you figured me out.

395
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:38,310
- l'm not on vacation, l'm broke.
- You're what?

396
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:41,916
Chapter 1 1 , my S and L crashed,
my creditors are after me.

397
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:46,153
- l gotta find a place to hide out.
- Why don't you hide out somewhere else?

398
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:49,630
Why don't you mind your own business?
Nobody asked you.

399
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:52,598
Wait, you can't be broke, we saw you on TV.

400
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:56,275
That was a big rip-off.
There were no franchises.

401
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:58,795
Hell, l only sold one starter kit.

402
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:03,988
l gotta find a place to lay low until
this whole godforsaken thing blows over.

403
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:07,357
Come on, Little Ben.
Do your old man a favour.

404
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:10,592
All those years l spent
putting a roof over your head.

405
00:27:10,760 --> 00:27:14,469
l even bribed that dean
to keep you in college, remember?

406
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:17,871
You know something? You owe me.

407
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:22,750
This room is a little small.

408
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:26,674
Well, it's all we've got.
You can sleep in one of the bunk-beds.

409
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:28,273
Or you can leave.

410
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:30,556
No, it'll do.

411
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:32,950
But l get the top bunk.

412
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:47,071
[snoring]

413
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:27,116
Finally!

414
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:35,471
[snoring]

415
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:53,592
Some educators
underestimate the value of civics,

416
00:28:53,760 --> 00:28:55,955
but l say, for the growing mind,

417
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:59,556
there's nothing more important
than pride in your city.

418
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:02,678
This is Highway 39.

419
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:06,115
This is the Mortville Steel Mill.

420
00:29:07,920 --> 00:29:12,038
And this is Mortville's very own Love Rock.

421
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:15,875
When the Dumore family settled this region,
they stole it from the lndians.

422
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:19,077
The lndians claim the rock has magic powers.

423
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:20,753
What kind of magic?

424
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:22,956
l don't know. Love magic, l guess.

425
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:27,591
You make a wish and it comes true,
at least that's what they tell the tourists.

426
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:30,638
[class laughs]

427
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:38,436
Can l get a drink of water?

428
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:40,397
Yes, you may, but hurry back.

429
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:44,109
l've got a great slide
of the Rotary Club coming straight up.

430
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:09,675
[guitar riff from Bad to the Bone]

431
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:17,036
Hey, pumpkin-head.

432
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:19,316
You're gonna wish you never said that.

433
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:21,072
Oh, yeah?

434
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:23,791
[screams]

435
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:31,271
So, what exactly happened?

436
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:33,351
l was using the fire hose.

437
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:36,830
Aha. And why were you doing this?

438
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:41,312
l told you, a fire had broken out
and l was trying to save the school.

439
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:44,916
Junior, what happened?

440
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:48,356
Your son saved the school. He put out a fire.

441
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:53,395
Did anyone ask him how it started? Because...

442
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:58,318
- l'm so sorry, that's very clumsy of me.
- That's OK.

443
00:30:59,160 --> 00:31:00,559
Listen...

444
00:31:01,520 --> 00:31:05,035
lf Junior seems a little troublesome lately,

445
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,758
l wouldn't worry about it.

446
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:11,357
He really hasn't made any friends here yet
so he's probably a little insecure.

447
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:14,919
Boy, you really know kids.

448
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:18,949
Junior and l were gonna get dinner later

449
00:31:19,120 --> 00:31:25,434
and l thought maybe if you didn't have
any plans that you'd...care to join us.

450
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:27,750
No, l can't.

451
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:29,114
Oh, well...

452
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:34,153
Maybe you and l
could do something Friday night?

453
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:36,675
l'd like to, but no.

454
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:40,959
- Saturday?
- No, not any night.

455
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:44,549
- l've got a problem.
- Excuse me?

456
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:48,395
- l can't go out with anyone.
- What if we just had dinner...

457
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:51,313
Dad! Didn't you hear the lady?
She's got a problem.

458
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:56,349
- Quit buggin' her and let's get out of here.
- Well, l... We'd better go.

459
00:31:56,520 --> 00:32:00,479
Anyway, it was nice talking to you,
Miss Young.

460
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:01,959
Annie.

461
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:05,669
lt was nice talking to you, too, Ben.
And Junior.

462
00:32:09,080 --> 00:32:13,392
''Can we go out on Friday night?
On Saturday night?''

463
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:15,312
''How about Sunday night?''

464
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:19,473
What's Dad's problem?
Doesn't he have any pride?

465
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:22,518
[girls] Lemonade! Fresh-squeezed lemonade!

466
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:28,312
Lemonade! Fresh-squeezed lemonade!

467
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,357
l'll have some lemonade.

468
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:33,273
[both] Certainly, that'll be two dollars.

469
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:36,519
l've only got a quarter.

470
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:39,592
Then l guess you're going thirsty, loser.

471
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:45,038
Dolly, there's no more lemonade.
Go back and fill it up.

472
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:48,351
l'm not gonna fill it up. Why don't you fill it up?

473
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:51,512
l'm not gonna fill it up. Why don't you fill it up?

474
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:55,593
Junior, why don't you go back and fill it up?

475
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:59,833
lf you do the work,
we might give you a free glass.

476
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:04,552
OK. l'll go fill it up.

477
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:18,395
[urinating into glass]

478
00:33:28,520 --> 00:33:31,478
[urinating continues]

479
00:33:47,320 --> 00:33:48,799
There you go, friends.

480
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:51,235
You only filled it halfway.

481
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:52,913
l tried my best.

482
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:56,868
That's not good enough.
For that, you don't get your free glass.

483
00:33:57,040 --> 00:33:59,270
That's OK by me.

484
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:04,631
[girls] Lemonade! Fresh-squeezed lemonade!

485
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:07,553
Boy, oh, boy. lt sure is hot.

486
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:10,837
l'm workin' up quite a sweat out here.

487
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:16,356
Dolly, Madison, how about
a glass of lemonade, huh?

488
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:18,829
Certainly. That'll be two dollars.

489
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:22,470
Two dollars?
For a glass of lemonade? For me?

490
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:26,110
Friggin' brats.

491
00:34:27,240 --> 00:34:28,639
Two dollars.

492
00:34:29,640 --> 00:34:31,471
All right, here you go.

493
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:50,557
Tangy.

494
00:34:55,280 --> 00:34:57,157
Dad, what do you want for dinner?

495
00:34:57,320 --> 00:35:01,871
- Macaroni and cheese or fish sticks?
- l'd love to have the fish sticks.

496
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:05,271
- But l got other plans.
- But l was making us dinner.

497
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:09,638
