My arms.

989
01:12:21,360 --> 01:12:23,237
My arms are free!

990
01:12:25,560 --> 01:12:26,959
Oh, my Lord.

991
01:12:27,880 --> 01:12:29,871
What's wrong with my face?

992
01:12:32,360 --> 01:12:34,112
What is this?

993
01:12:45,080 --> 01:12:48,072
Oh... Oh!

994
01:12:50,480 --> 01:12:53,074
[LaWanda] l'm Pinocchio!

995
01:13:05,800 --> 01:13:07,950
Good, you made it.

996
01:13:08,120 --> 01:13:10,680
Why did you want me to come over so late?

997
01:13:10,840 --> 01:13:13,752
- You know how you said you liked my dad?
- Yeah.

998
01:13:13,920 --> 01:13:17,469
l have the weirdest idea.
l think our parents should get married.

999
01:13:17,640 --> 01:13:22,589
What are you talking about?
Your dad's already taken.

1000
01:13:22,760 --> 01:13:26,594
Well, he might be having
a slight change of plans.

1001
01:13:26,760 --> 01:13:29,752
[snoring and growling]

1002
01:13:31,120 --> 01:13:33,634
Oh, great. Big Ben's up.

1003
01:13:34,760 --> 01:13:38,150
Who are you? And you should be in bed,

1004
01:13:38,320 --> 01:13:39,992
resting up for tomorrow's wedding.

1005
01:13:40,160 --> 01:13:41,752
There ain't gonna be no wedding.

1006
01:13:41,920 --> 01:13:45,799
l made LaWanda so ugly,
no one's gonna wanna marry her.

1007
01:13:45,960 --> 01:13:48,428
LaWanda Dumore's the key
to my financial comeback.

1008
01:13:48,600 --> 01:13:52,513
And nobody, nobody,
is gonna stand in my way.

1009
01:13:54,440 --> 01:13:57,876
- Nippy, where'd you go?
- This guy's gonna be a problem.

1010
01:13:58,040 --> 01:14:00,952
No, he's not. Let's get him!

1011
01:14:01,120 --> 01:14:02,269
Yeah!

1012
01:14:16,840 --> 01:14:18,956
l'm really tired.

1013
01:14:19,960 --> 01:14:24,192
Come on, don't wuss out. This is
the only way to get our parents together.

1014
01:14:24,360 --> 01:14:26,157
Now come on!

1015
01:14:36,240 --> 01:14:40,472
Whoa! lt's so much bigger
than it looked on Mr Thorn's slide.

1016
01:14:44,480 --> 01:14:46,675
So, how do you start this thing?

1017
01:14:46,840 --> 01:14:49,957
l don't know. Guess you just make a wish.

1018
01:14:50,120 --> 01:14:54,033
Mighty Love Rock,
we come to you today to ask a big favour.

1019
01:14:54,200 --> 01:14:58,193
We got two parents and we want them
to fall in love and get married

1020
01:14:58,360 --> 01:15:00,635
so l don't get stuck with that bitch LaWanda.

1021
01:15:00,800 --> 01:15:03,917
l hope this isn't asking too much,

1022
01:15:04,080 --> 01:15:08,119
but you're a magic rock
so you're probably used to these things.

1023
01:15:08,280 --> 01:15:10,589
Please help us.

1024
01:15:37,040 --> 01:15:38,553
Bye, Annie.

1025
01:15:44,920 --> 01:15:46,990
All right, Junior. Get up.

1026
01:15:47,160 --> 01:15:50,914
lt's a big day. Today you get yourself a mom.

1027
01:15:51,080 --> 01:15:53,071
[phone]

1028
01:15:53,440 --> 01:15:55,954
Has Junior ever run away before?

1029
01:15:56,120 --> 01:16:00,636
No, it's this wedding thing. lt's got him upset.
l'm sorry he dragged Trixie into this.

1030
01:16:00,800 --> 01:16:05,316
Don't let Trixie off the hook. She's usually
responsible for her share of the action.

1031
01:16:05,480 --> 01:16:08,278
Junior can be
the biggest menace who ever lived.

1032
01:16:08,440 --> 01:16:12,877
Well, maybe he was a nuisance
in that little town you're from.

1033
01:16:13,040 --> 01:16:15,793
You're in Mortville
and around here Trixie runs the show.

1034
01:16:15,960 --> 01:16:20,511
She's an amateur. Nobody has caused
the amount of destruction Junior has.

1035
01:16:22,200 --> 01:16:25,158
l guess it's a stupid thing to argue about.

1036
01:16:28,800 --> 01:16:30,392
There they are.

1037
01:16:44,760 --> 01:16:47,194
Will you look at that?

1038
01:16:47,360 --> 01:16:49,828
Hey, guys. Good morning.

1039
01:16:52,720 --> 01:16:56,235
Hey, the Love Rock worked!

1040
01:16:56,400 --> 01:16:59,517
Up and at 'em, Junior, let's go. Attaboy.

1041
01:17:04,840 --> 01:17:07,957
So, do you need a ride home?

1042
01:17:08,120 --> 01:17:12,352
No, l think we're gonna take a little walk
and have a little talk.

1043
01:17:12,520 --> 01:17:15,637
Besides, you've probably
got millions of things to do today.

1044
01:17:15,800 --> 01:17:18,792
Yeah, l guess l do have plans.

1045
01:17:18,960 --> 01:17:21,758
So, see ya.

1046
01:17:38,320 --> 01:17:41,232
Typical, Little Ben.
You always wait till the last damn minute.

1047
01:17:41,400 --> 01:17:44,073
Dad, don't you wanna go see LaWanda?

1048
01:17:44,240 --> 01:17:47,755
There's a tradition. The groom
can't see the bride before the ceremony.

1049
01:17:47,920 --> 01:17:50,514
- But...but...
- But...but, my ass.

1050
01:17:50,680 --> 01:17:52,910
Beat it, we're busy.

1051
01:17:53,080 --> 01:17:56,789
Oh, nol lf Dad doesn't see
LaWanda's big schnozz,

1052
01:17:56,960 --> 01:17:58,791
l'm screwed.

1053
01:18:01,880 --> 01:18:03,871
[music: wedding march]

1054
01:18:48,800 --> 01:18:50,313
Miss Dumore!

1055
01:18:52,080 --> 01:18:54,992
- Are you all right?
- Dad, look at her face.

1056
01:18:57,760 --> 01:18:59,716
Hey, what happened?

1057
01:18:59,880 --> 01:19:01,996
Thought you had me licked, huh?

1058
01:19:02,160 --> 01:19:04,879
lt's amazing what $382,000 worth

1059
01:19:05,040 --> 01:19:08,476
of last-minute double overtime
plastic surgery can do.

1060
01:19:10,600 --> 01:19:12,636
Benjamin, what's the hold-up?

1061
01:19:13,920 --> 01:19:15,239
Fine.

1062
01:19:16,120 --> 01:19:18,918
Come on, sit down, kid.

1063
01:19:19,080 --> 01:19:20,593
Hit it, padre.

1064
01:19:24,120 --> 01:19:27,749
Dearly beloved, we are gathered today,
on this day of joy,

1065
01:19:27,920 --> 01:19:30,070
to unite these two wonderful people.

1066
01:19:30,240 --> 01:19:32,595
No! Dad, don't do it!

1067
01:19:32,760 --> 01:19:35,320
Go for it, Little Ben. Make me proud!

1068
01:19:39,400 --> 01:19:42,278
We are gathered together
on this day of joy,

1069
01:19:42,440 --> 01:19:44,670
- to unite you two wonderful p...
- [horn beeps]

1070
01:19:49,800 --> 01:19:51,392
Who the hell is that?

1071
01:19:51,560 --> 01:19:53,516
That's my pal Trixie.

1072
01:19:57,000 --> 01:19:58,991
[horn]

1073
01:20:01,080 --> 01:20:03,116
l hate children!

1074
01:20:03,280 --> 01:20:05,510
They ruin everything!

1075
01:20:05,680 --> 01:20:10,515
lf l had enough power,
l'd wipe them off the face of the earth.

1076
01:20:14,280 --> 01:20:16,589
[screaming]

1077
01:20:23,200 --> 01:20:24,349
Junior!

1078
01:20:32,800 --> 01:20:34,438
Nippy! No!

1079
01:20:42,000 --> 01:20:43,877
No, Miss Dumore! No!

1080
01:20:46,880 --> 01:20:48,632
l command you to stop.

1081
01:20:51,360 --> 01:20:55,194
Trixie! You come down here
right this minute!

1082
01:20:57,040 --> 01:21:00,749
How many times have l told you
not to operate heavy machinery?

1083
01:21:00,920 --> 01:21:03,718
- Annie!
- Ben, l am so sorry.

1084
01:21:03,880 --> 01:21:06,633
l couldn't stop her.
We've ruined your whole wedding.

1085
01:21:06,800 --> 01:21:10,713
This wedding was meant to be ruined.
Annie, you're the one l want.

1086
01:21:11,920 --> 01:21:13,239
What?

1087
01:21:16,120 --> 01:21:18,475
- Yeah!
- We did it!

1088
01:21:19,000 --> 01:21:23,790
What the hell are you doing? You gotta
scrape your lovely bride off the ground.

1089
01:21:23,960 --> 01:21:27,509
Dad, l don't want to marry LaWanda.
l've found someone else.

1090
01:21:27,680 --> 01:21:31,958
Who cares? LaWanda Dumore
is a gold-mine. She's worth millions.

1091
01:21:32,120 --> 01:21:34,588
Dad, if you like her so much, you marry her.

1092
01:21:34,760 --> 01:21:36,193
[ching of cash register]

1093
01:21:36,360 --> 01:21:38,669
Yeah. Why not?

1094
01:21:45,520 --> 01:21:46,839
Thanks, buddy.

1095
01:21:47,000 --> 01:21:50,072
Dad, l wouldn't have done it for anyone else.

1096
01:21:54,600 --> 01:21:55,919
Let me help you.

1097
01:21:56,080 --> 01:21:58,833
One...two...three...

1098
01:22:04,080 --> 01:22:05,638
Let me help you.

1099
01:22:05,800 --> 01:22:07,791
Not you, dummy.

1100
01:22:08,800 --> 01:22:10,358
Come on, there we go.

1101
01:22:10,520 --> 01:22:12,511
Get your mitts off me.

1102
01:22:12,680 --> 01:22:14,830
l hate your whole family.

1103
01:22:15,000 --> 01:22:18,231
Honey, come here. l'm not like them.

1104
01:22:18,400 --> 01:22:21,278
l'm different. l love you.

1105
01:22:22,760 --> 01:22:25,228
You said you love me?

1106
01:22:27,880 --> 01:22:29,199
Yeuch!

1107
01:22:43,600 --> 01:22:44,635
Yeah!

1108
01:22:51,200 --> 01:22:53,350
Nippy!

1109
01:22:53,520 --> 01:22:56,432
Oh, my God.

1110
01:22:57,240 --> 01:22:59,231
[song: Saved By Love]

